{
  "texts": [
    "In the realm of wastewater treatment, thiazine dyes such as methylene blue play a crucial role in addressing environmental concerns (Paul and Suresh Kumar, 2013).",
    "Notably, thiazine dyes exhibit unique properties, including solva-tochromism and metachrosis, making them highly sensitive to changes in their surroundings.",
    "Additionally, their high singlet oxygen quantum yields contribute to their efficacy in specific applications.",
    "In the context of wastewater treatment, these dyes can be strategically modified to create derivatives with enhanced functionality, allowing for the introduction of new substituents at the nitrogen or CH groups (Montalti et al., 2006; Talman and Atun, 2006).",
    "As such, thiazine dyes, like many other synthetic dyes, have both advantages and disadvantages in various applications, including their use in water-based systems."
  ]
}